(44, 2, 27, 43, 11, 39, 39, 'see corruption', 'Resurrection and Corruption', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection, as Acts 2:27 speaks of not allowing the Holy One to see corruption, while John 11:39 emphasizes the decay of Lazarus after four days of death. Both passages underscore the contrast between life and death.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
